{{refimprove|date=February 2014}}
The '''1988 Lifesaving World Championships''' were  held between 22-27 March 1988 at the [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].

These were the first [[World Life Saving Championships|Lifesaving World Championships]] to include both pool and ocean events with the pool events being conducted at the [[Southport Olympic Pool]] in [[Southport, Queensland|Southport]] and the ocean events being conducted at [[Main Beach, Queensland|Main Beach]] and [[Greenmount Beach]]. As well as being the first championships to include both pool and ocean lifesaving events, these were the first championships to conduct contests for both Interclub and International teams. Competitors representing teams from 10 countries including [[Australia]], [[Canada]], [[Germany]], [[Great Britain]], [[Indonesia]], [[Japan]], [[New Zealand]], [[Sri Lanka]], [[Taiwan]], and the [[United States]] took part.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lifesaving Sport History|url=http://www.rlss.org.uk/index.php/lifesaving-sport/what-is-lifesaving-sport/lifesavingsporthistory|publisher=[[Royal Life Saving Society UK]]|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref>

The '''National Teams''' competition included 5 pool and 11 ocean events, whilst the '''Interclub''' competition included 8 men's pool events, 13 men's ocean events, and 3 women's ocean events.  Competitors from Australia dominated the competitions.

