The '''[[1995 CFL season|1995]] [[CFL Draft]]''' composed of seven rounds and 55 [[Canadian football]] players that were chosen from eligible [[List of universities in Canada|Canadian universities]] as well as Canadian players playing in the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]]. The first eight picks of the draft were part of a "bonus round" awarded to teams who had complied with the Competitive Expenditure Cap. The following round, consisting of picks 9-16, was the regular first round of the draft.
