'''F.C. Boca Gibraltar''' is a football team from [[Gibraltar]]. They play in the [[Gibraltar Premier Division]] having previously played in the [[Gibraltar Second Division]] and they also play in the [[Rock Cup]].<ref>http://gibraltarfa.com/domestic-football/cup/rock-cup</ref>

==History==
The club was founded as '''Boca Juniors Gibraltar F.C.''' in 2012, and joined the [[Gibraltar Second Division]] for the 2012-13 season. After the [[Gibraltar Football Association]] joined [[UEFA]] in 2013, the league saw significant expansion and an influx of foreign players, however, a 10th place finish in the 14 team league was all they could muster in the [[2014–15 Gibraltar Second Division|2014–15 season]]. After rebuilding the squad in the now 12 team division, the team finished 8th in the [[2015–16 Gibraltar Second Division|2015–16 season]].

Significant improvements after the departure of [[Red Imps F.C.|Red Imps]], [[Pegasus F.C.|Pegasus]] and [[F.C. Britannia XI|Britannia]] from the league saw an impressive 3rd place finish in 2017, while the club began referring to themselves as simply '''Boca Gibraltar'''. However, 7 points separated Boca from the top two teams, and they missed out on the promotion play-off. A restructuring in summer 2017 saw former goalkeeper and club captain Philip Hermida promoted to Director of Football, with the intention of challenging for promotion in 2018. A 1-1 draw with Ocean Village rivals [[F.C. Bruno's Magpies|Bruno's Magpies]] on the final day secured the Second Division title by a single point on 22 May 2018, ensuring that Boca will play in the [[Gibraltar Premier Division]] for the first time next season.

