'''Kelantan Football Association (Piala Tun Sharifah Rodziah)''' is a women's football team from [[Kota Bharu]] representing the state of [[Kelantan]]. Founded in 2017, the team competes in [[Piala Tun Sharifah Rodziah]]. 2017 is their debut appearance in the competition managed by the [[Football Association of Malaysia]] (FAM).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bharian.com.my/node/262956 | publisher = [[Berita Harian]] | title = 12 pasukan rebut Piala Tun Sharifah Rodziah | date = 22 March 2017 | accessdate = 2 April 2017}}</ref>

==History==
The '''Kelantan Football Association (Piala Tun Sharifah Rodziah)''' team or '''Kelantan FA women's football team''' was formed in 2017 originally for the preparation of [[Tun Sharifah Rodziah Cup]] tournament. The team consist former [[Liga Bolasepak Rakyat|Liga Bolasepak Rakyat Wanita]] players, who represented the club in state of [[Kelantan]] and others via players selection on 11 March 2017 at the [[University of Science, Malaysia]] Mini Stadium, [[Kubang Kerian]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=1840586136161946&id=1838277866392773 | publisher = Bolasepak Wanita Kelantan| title = Sesi pemilihan pemain | date = 11 March 2017 | accessdate = 2 April 2017}}</ref> The 2017 Piala Tun Sharifah Rodziah tournament will be held in [[Miri, Malaysia|Miri]], [[Sarawak]] starting 6 April until 16 April 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fam.org.my/news/miri-venue-saingan-piala-tun-sharifah-rodziah-2017 | publisher = [[Football Association of Malaysia|FAM]] | title = Miri venue saingan Piala Tun Sharifah Rodziah 2017 | date = 8 March 2017 | accessdate = 2 April 2017}}</ref> 12 teams have confirmed their participation in the tournament. During 2017 tournament, the teams were divided into three groups and Kelantan were draw into Group C along with Sarawak, Pahang and Negeri Sembilan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.utusanborneo.com.my/2017/03/28/skuad-wanita-sarawak-diundi-bersama-ns-pahang-dan-kelantan | publisher = Utusan Borneo| title = Skuad Wanita Sarawak diundi bersama NS, Pahang dan Kelantan | date = 28 March 2017 | accessdate = 5 April 2017}}</ref>

Kelantan FA women's team was not eligible for the knockout stage after two defeats and a draw in the group stage. They gained third-placed in the table with 1 goal and conceded 6 goals along the campaign. The only goal scored was during the draw against [[Negeri Sembilan FA|Negeri Sembilan]] by Siti Hajar Mat Zaid.

