'''Omar Mohamed Omar''' ({{lang-so|Cumar Maxamed Cumar}}, {{lang-ar|عمر محمد عمر}}) (1970 - 25 December 2008), also known as '''Anyeelo''',  was a [[Somali people|Somali]] basketball player and coach. He was coach of the Somali national team from 2007 until his death.<ref>[http://somsoccer.com/english/view.php?id=77 Somali Football federation sends a condolences message to Somali people over the death of two sporting veterans.] SomSoccer.com, 27 December 2008</ref> A member and coach of the [[Somalia national basketball team]], Omar died in a car crash in [[England]] on 25 December 2008.<ref>[http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fc/news/lateNews/p/langid/1/newsid/29199/arti.html Former Somalia player, coach Mohamed dies in car crash] FIBA.com, 8 January 2009</ref>

